OL,3,CRate of women being hired into top
OL,4,Cjobs falls for third year running `
OL,5,CLinkedIn
OL,7,FThe figures suggest it becomes more
OL,8,Fdifficult for older generations to
OL,9,Freach senior management, with 19.4% of
OL,10,Fso-called baby boomers ` those born
OL,11,Fbetween 1946 and 1964 ` in these roles
OL,12,Fcompared with 28.9% for gen X, 36.7%
OL,13,Ffor millennials and 39.3% for gen Z.
OL,15,FThe statistics, compiled by analysing
OL,16,Fthe group's 43 million-strong
OL,17,Fmembership base across the UK, also
OL,18,Fshow that, as of March, women made up
OL,19,F45.8% of hires in the UK, down 4.6%
OL,20,Fyear-on-year.
